Subject: Start up requested (ASRT)
Source Text: The time that start up is requested (ASRT).

Subject: ATC confirms TSAT to pilot
Source Text: ATC confirms TSAT to the pilot in order to maintain the aircraft in the pre-departure sequence.

Subject: ATC assures regulated flight respects CTOT
Source Text: Provided the aircraft was ready on time (ARDT), it is now up to ATC to assure that a regulated flight can respect its CTOT.

Subject: Inform CDM Partners of ASRT in ACISP
Source Text: First step: To inform all relevant Airport CDM Partners of Actual Start up Request Time (ASRT) in the Airport CDM Platform.

Subject: Alert CDM Partners if no start up requested within TSAT tolerance
Source Text: Second step: to alert all relevant Airport CDM Partners when no start up has been requested inside the locally agreed TSAT tolerance window.

Subject: AO/GH informed of no start up request
Source Text: If the start up request is not made by TSAT + tolerance, the AO/GH is informed that no start up has been requested
